<item>
            <title>[FLINK-36959] Computing readable buffer offsets and sizes when including empty buffers fails.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-36959</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The computation of readable buffer offsets and sizes fails when the range starts or ends with empty buffers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The offsets and sizes of buffers can follow these patterns:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
{{0,0}, ..., {1,3}, ..., {0,0}, {5,6}, ...} &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; non-broadcast scenarios.&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
{{1,2}, ..., {1,2}, ..., {1,2}, ...}&#160;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; broadcast scenarios. &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, the current logic does not correctly handle situations where the sequence starts or ends with an empty buffer. This needs to be fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
